{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang2057\f0\fs20 Who fathoms the eternal thought?
\par Who talks of scheme and plan?
\par The Lord is God! He needeth not
\par The poor device of man.
\par }

Verse2:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang2057\f0\fs20 I see the wrong that round me lies,
\par I feel the guilt within.
\par I hear, with groan and travail-cries,
\par The world confess its sin.
\par }

Verse3:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang2057\f0\fs20 Yet, in the maddening maze of things,
\par And tossed by storm and flood,
\par To one fixed stake my spirit clings;
\par I know that God is good!
\par }

Verse4:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang2057\f0\fs20 And if my heart and flesh are weak
\par To bear an untried pain,
\par The bruised reed he will not break,
\par But strengthen and sustain.
\par }

Verse5:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang2057\f0\fs20 I know not what the future hath
\par Of marvel or surprise,
\par Assured alone that life and death
\par His mercy underlies.
\par }

Verse1:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang2057\f0\fs20 I am fearfully and wonderfully made
\par I am fearfully and wonderfully made
\par He who put the stars in place
\par And knows them all by name
\par Has made me fearfully and wonderfully made.
\par }

Verse2:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang2057\f0\fs20 I am made in the image of God
\par I am made in the image of God
\par From the top of my head to the tips of my toes
\par My Lord, my name He knows
\par I am made in the image of God.
\par }

Verse3:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang2057{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs20 
\par }

Verse4:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang2057{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs20 
\par }

Verse1:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang2057\f0\fs20 Your hand, O God has guided
\par Your flock, from age to age;
\par Your faithfulness is written
\par On history's open page.
\par Our fathers knew Your goodness,
\par And we their deeds record;
\par And both to this bear witness
\par One church, one faith, One Lord
\par }

Verse2:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang2057\f0\fs20 Your heralds brought the gospel
\par To greatest as to least;
\par They summoned men to hasten
\par And share the great king's feast
\par And this was all their teaching
\par In every deed and word;
\par To all alike proclaiming
\par One church, one faith, One Lord
\par }

Verse3:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang2057\f0\fs20 Through many days of darkness,
\par Through many scenes of strife,
\par The faithful few fought bravely
\par To guard the nation's life.
\par Their gospel of redemption
\par Sin pardoned, man restored;
\par Was all in this enfolded.
\par One church, one faith, One Lord
\par }

Verse4:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang2057\f0\fs20 Your mercy will not fail us
\par Nor leave Your work undone;
\par With Your right hand to help us,
\par The victory shall be won
\par And then by earth and heaven
\par Your name shall be adored;
\par And this shall be their anthem
\par One church, one faith, One Lord.
\par }

Verse1:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang1033\f0\fs20 Thy life was given for me!
\par Thy blood, O Lord, was shed
\par That I might ransomed be,
\par And quickened from the dead.
\par Thy life was given for me:
\par What have I given for Thee?
\par }

Verse2:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang2057\f0\fs20 Long years were spent for me
\par In weariness and woe,
\par That through eternity
\par Thy glory I might know.
\par Long years were spent for me:
\par Have I spent one for Thee?
\par }

Verse3:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang2057\f0\fs20 Thy Father's home of light,
\par Thy rainbow-circled throne,
\par Were left for earthly night
\par For wanderings sad and lone.
\par Yea, all, was left for me:
\par Have I left ought for Thee?
\par }

Verse4:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang2057\f0\fs20 Thou, Lord, hast borne for me
\par More than my tongue can tell
\par Of bitterest agony,
\par To rescue me from hell.
\par Thou suff'redst all for me:
\par What have I borne for Thee!
\par }

Verse5:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang2057\f0\fs20 And Thou hast brought to me,
\par Down from Thy home above,
\par Salvation full and free,
\par Thy pardon and Thy love.
\par Great gifts Thou broughtest me:
\par What have I brought to Thee!
\par }

Verse6:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang2057\f0\fs20 Oh, let my life be given,
\par My years for Thee be spent;
\par World-fetters all be riven,
\par And joy with suffering blent:
\par To Thee my all I bring.
\par My Saviour and my King!
\par }

Verse1:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang1033\f0\fs20 You're the God that pursues me
\par That heals me
\par That loves
\par You're the God that walks with me
\par Befriends me
\par That knows
\par }

Verse2:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang1033\f0\fs20 Worship brings You close to me
\par I'm ready now to believe
\par Available to receive
\par The seed of faith, a touch of grace,
\par }

Verse3:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang1033\f0\fs20 You're the God that pursues us
\par That heals us
\par That loves
\par You're the God that walks with us
\par Befriends us
\par That knows
\par }

Verse4:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0\deflang2057{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\f0\fs20 
\par }

Chorus:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang1033\f0\fs20 Giving You worship is my perfect chance
\par To receive You with an open heart
\par Devotion in worship is Your perfect chance
\par To transform our brokenness inside
\par Singing Your song over me
\par Sing Your song - Redeemers mercy
\par }

Verse1:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang2057\f0\fs20 Come people of the risen King,
\par Who delight to bring Him praise;
\par Come all and tune your hearts to sing
\par To the Morning Star of grace.
\par From the shifting shadows of the earth
\par We will lift our eyes to Him,
\par Where steady arms of mercy reach
\par To gather children in.
\par }

Verse2:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang2057\f0\fs20 Rejoice, Rejoice! Let every tongue rejoice
\par One heart, one voice;
\par O Church of Christ, rejoice!
\par }

Verse3:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang2057\f0\fs20 Come, those whose joy is morning sun,
\par And those weeping through the night;
\par Come, those who tell of battles won,
\par And those struggling in the fight.
\par For His perfect love will never change,
\par And His mercies never cease,
\par But follow us through all our days
\par With the certain hope of peace.
\par }

Verse4:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang2057\f0\fs20 Come, young and old from every land -
\par Men and women of the faith;
\par Come, those with full or empty hands -
\par Find the riches of His grace.
\par Over all the world, His people sing -
\par Shore to shore we hear them call
\par The Truth that cries through every age:
\par "Our God is all in all"!
\par }

Verse1:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang2057\f0\fs20 Lover of my soul, I run to You
\par Captor of my heart, I worship You
\par Maker of my dreams, I live for You
\par Lord of all I am, I give to You
\par }

Verse2:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang1033\f0\fs20 For You are good
\par For You are true
\par Almighty God
\par You never change
\par You never fail
\par For You are love
\par }

Verse3:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang1033\f0\fs20 Steadfast Saviour
\par My Redeemer
\par Ever faithful God
\par Forever You are, everlasting God
\par }

Verse4:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang1033\f0\fs20 Beginning and end, I honour You
\par Giver of life, I follow You
\par King who reigns on high,
\par There's none like You
\par Lord of all I am, I give to You
\par }

Verse5:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang1033\f0\fs20 Rock of ages
\par My salvation
\par Ever faithful God
\par }

Verse1:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang2057\f0\fs20 Mountain maker, ocean tamer
\par Glimpses of You burn in my eyes
\par The worship of heaven
\par Fills up the skies
\par }

Verse3:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang2057\f0\fs20 Star creator, wind breather
\par The strokes of Your beauty
\par Brushed through the clouds
\par Light from the heavens
\par Touching the ground
\par }

Verse4:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang2057\f0\fs20 Imagination runs wild
\par And breathes the breath of life
\par Across the fields, across the miles
\par }

Verse1:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang1033\f0\fs20 Looks like the river's turned
\par Walk out on bridges burned
\par I'm sorry, I'm sorry
\par }

Verse2:
{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 MS Sans Serif;}}
{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\lang1033\f0\fs20 Looks like the fire has burnt
\par Dried all the tears that come
\par I'm sorry, I'm sorry
\par }

